 this is best-effort for hook paths.\\nfunc prepareTranscriptIfNeeded(ctx context.Context, ag agent.Agent, transcriptPath string) {\\n\\tif ag == nil || transcriptPath == \\\"\\\" {\\n\\t\\treturn\\n\\t}\\n\\tif preparer, ok := ag.(agent.TranscriptPreparer); ok {\\n\\t\\t// Best-effort: callers handle missing files gracefully.\\n\\t\\t// Transcript may not be available yet (e.g., agent not installed).\\n\\t\\t_ = preparer.PrepareTranscript(ctx, transcriptPath) //nolint:errcheck // Best-effort in hook path\\n\\t}\\n}\\n\",\"numLines\":17,\"startLine\":1424,\"totalLines\":1440}},\"sourceToolAssistantUUID\":\"f2b1f852-69a1-4505-a03e-6c989d027efd\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"694df03e-52c2-489b-a283-bdf785783d04\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/alex/workspace/cli/.worktrees/2\",\"sessionId\":\"85d2e85c-7fb0-4205-9bd7-0f6cc5d2c405\",\"version\":\"2.1.63\",\"gitBranch\":\"soph/transcript-wait-bug-the-second\",\"slug\":\"memoized-floating-perlis\",\"message\":{\"model\":\"claude-opus-4-6\",\"id\":\"msg_01NEHN5KedsUATyaA7oLfmQG\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"---\\n\\n## PR #545 Review: Stale transcript file skip in `waitForTranscriptFlush`\\n\\n### Overview\\n\\nThis PR adds a fast-path check to `waitForTranscriptFlush` that skips the 3-second polling loop when the transcript file is either nonexistent or stale (mtime > 2 minutes old). This prevents unnecessary blocking during post-commit hooks when a Claude Code session has ended or crashed without firing its stop hook.\\n\\n### Analysis\\n\\n**The fix is correct and well-scoped.** The logic is sound:\\n\\n1. If the file doesn't exist → nothing to wait for → return immediately\\n2. If the file hasn't been modified in 2+ minutes → the agent clearly isn't running → return immediately\\n3. Otherwise → fall through to the existing polling loop\\n\\nThe 2-minute threshold is generous — Claude Code writes to the transcript continuously during active use, so a 2-minute gap is a strong signal the agent is no longer running.\\n\\n### Issues\\n\\n**1. Silent swallowing of all `os.Stat` errors (minor)**\\n\\n```go\\ninfo, err := os.Stat(transcriptPath)\\nif err != nil {\\n    return // file doesn't exist, nothing to wait for\\n}\\n```\\n\\nThe comment says \\\"file doesn't exist\\\" but `os.Stat` can fail for other reasons (permission errors, path too long, etc.). In those cases the existing poll loop might have succeeded since `os.Open` inside `checkStopSentinel` could behave differently. This is a minor concern since:\\n- The function is already best-effort (falls back silently after timeout)\\n- Permission errors would also cause `checkStopSentinel` to fail\\n- In practice, the only realistic error here is `ENOENT`\\n\\nI'd suggest at minimum updating the comment to be accurate, and optionally logging non-`ENOENT` errors:\\n\\n```go\\nif err != nil {\\n    // Can't stat the file — most likely doesn't exist. Either way, polling\\n    // won't help, so skip the wait.\\n    return\\n}\\n```\\n\\n**2. Tests use wall-clock timing (acceptable but fragile)**\\n\\nThe tests assert `elapsed < 500ms` for the fast path and `elapsed > 2s` for the slow path. These are reasonable on a dev machine but could flake on very slow CI runners. The 500ms vs 3s gap gives plenty of room, so this is acceptable in practice.\\n\\n### What looks good\\n\\n- Clean separation of the fast-path check before the polling loop\\n- Good logging — the stale case logs a debug message with the file age\\n- Three well-structured test cases covering each branch (stale, recent, nonexistent)\\n- Tests use `t.Parallel()` per project conventions\\n- The PR description clearly documents known follow-ups that are out of scope\\n\\n### Summary\\n\\n**Approve with minor nit.** The fix is correct, targeted, and well-tested. The only suggestion is to make the error handling comment more accurate (it's not just \\\"file doesn't exist\\\"). The follow-ups mentioned in the PR description (stale session cleanup, large transcript optimization) are appropriate to defer.\"}],\"stop_reason\":\"end_turn\",\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":1,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":414,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":66638,\"output_tokens\":718,\"server_tool_use\":{\"web_search_requests\":0,\"web_fetch_requests\":0},\"service_tier\":\"standard\",\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":414,\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0},\"inference_geo\":\"\",\"iterations\":[],\"speed\":\"standard\"}},\"requestId\":\"req_011CYdGuo5LkHesvxSLB5ZUg\",\"type\":\"assistant\",\"uuid\":\"5e55bfed-c63d-462d-9f61-1f3b7842f273\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-02T00:04:33.391Z\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"5e55bfed-c63d-462d-9f61-1f3b7842f273\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/alex/workspace/cli/.worktrees/2\",\"sessionId\":\"85d2e85c-7fb0-4205-9bd7-0f6cc5d2c405\",\"version\":\"2.1.63\",\"gitBranch\":\"soph/transcript-wait-bug-the-second\",\"slug\":\"memoized-floating-perlis\",\"type\":\"progress\",\"data\":{\"type\":\"hook_progress\",\"hookEvent\":\"Stop\",\"hookName\":\"Stop\",\"command\":\"go run ${CLAUDE_PROJECT_DIR}/cmd/entire/main.go hooks claude-code stop\"},\"parentToolUseID\":\"59ece4cb-a996-4ef9-83db-4f09e1a404a5\",\"toolUseID\":\"59ece4cb-a996-4ef9-83db-4f09e1a404a5\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-02T00:04:33.432Z\",\"uuid\":\"ff54903e-9e18-4403-8f8a-2365de42e992\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"ff54903e-9e18-4403-8f8a-2365de42e992\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/alex/workspace/cli/.worktrees/2\",\"sessionId\":\"85d2e85c-7fb0-4205-9bd7-0f6cc5d2c405\",\"version\":\"2.1.63\",\"gitBranch\":\"soph/transcript-wait-bug-the-second\",\"slug\":\"memoized-floating-perlis\",\"type\":\"system\",\"subtype\":\"stop_hook_summary\",\"hookCount\":1,\"hookInfos\":[{\"command\":\"go run ${CLAUDE_PROJECT_DIR}/cmd/entire/main.go hooks claude-code stop\",\"durationMs\":482}],\"hookErrors\":[],\"preventedContinuation\":